       8. ML Feature Engineering Recommendations

       Categorical Features:

       - pitch_type (from venue)
       - bowler_style (pace/spin variants)
       - shot_type (12+ types)
       - delivery_type (12+ types)
       - venue_name (11 venues) or venue_key
       - batsman_role (opener, middle-order, finisher, bowler)
       - batsman_batting_style (RHB/LHB)
       - Is phase (powerplay/middle/death) from over number

       Numerical Features:

       1. Game State: over, ball_in_over, balls_faced, partnership_runs, target_gap
       2. Player Stats: batsman_SR, batsman_avg, bowler_economy, bowler_avg
       3. Pitch Conditions: batting_ease, pace_eff, spin_eff, bounce_consistency
       4. Weather: humidity, wind_speed, cloud_cover, swing_factor, dew_factor
       5. Player Traits: aggression, pressure_resilience, form_confidence, experience_years, age
       6. Pressure: pressure_index, wickets_fallen, runs_needed_per_ball
       7. Venue: boundary_asymmetry, dew_factor, chase_win_rate
       8. Fatigue: batsman_fatigue, bowler_fatigue
       9. Field: deep_fielders_count, slips_count

       Target Variables:

       1. Regression: runs (0-6) with continuous weighting
       2. Multi-class: outcome_key ∈ {dot, single, two, three, boundary, six, wicket}
       3. Binary: is_wicket (True/False)
       4. Hierarchical: runs (0-6), then given is_wicket, then dismissal_type

       Interaction Features Worth Engineering:

       - bowler_economy × pressure_index (pressure amplifies good bowlers)
       - batsman_aggression × collapse_active (collapse suppresses natural aggression)
       - pitch_batting_ease × bowler_death_spec (tight pitches penalize death specialists less)
       - dew_factor × spin_effectiveness (dew reduces spin grip)
       - partner_sr × this_batter_sr (mismatch triggers anchor penalty)
       - age × experience_years (veterans age better)
       - boundary_asymmetry × shot_direction (asymmetry applies to direction-specific shots)

