       10. Probability Distributions Vs Deterministic Models

       The current system uses probabilistic sampling from adjusted weights:
       - OutcomeResolver: 7 modifier layers → normalized probabilities → sample outcome
       - PlayerAgent.bat(): 25+ modifier layers → normalized → sample outcome

       For CatBoost:
       - Train on simulated outcomes to approximate the weight adjustments
       - Predict P(runs=k) and P(wicket) directly
       - Can then sample from CatBoost's predicted probabilities for stochastic simulation

       This gives you:
       - Explainability (feature importance ranking)
       - Generalization beyond hard-coded rules
       - Calibration via probability predictions
       - Flexibility to extend to unseen player/venue combos

